com.appetizeapp.android.util

Class AndroidHttpClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.appetizeapp.android.util.AndroidHttpClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.http.client.HttpClient

    public final class AndroidHttpClient
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.http.client.HttpClient
    Subclass of the Apache DefaultHttpClient that is configured with reasonable default settings and registered schemes for Android, and also lets the user add HttpRequestInterceptor classes. Don't create this directly, use the newInstance(java.lang.String, android.content.Context) factory method.

    This client processes cookies but does not retain them by default. To retain cookies, simply add a cookie store to the HttpContext:

    context.setAttribute(ClientContext.COOKIE_STORE, cookieStore);

      • parseDate

        public static long parseDate(java.lang.String dateString)
        Returns the date of the given HTTP date string. This method can identify and parse the date formats emitted by common HTTP servers, such as RFC 822, RFC 850, RFC 1036, RFC 1123 and ANSI C's asctime().
        Returns:
        the number of milliseconds since Jan. 1, 1970, midnight GMT.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if dateString is not a date or of an unsupported format.
